# =============================================================================
# PRODUCTION ENVIRONMENT CONFIGURATION FOR VERCEL DEPLOYMENT
# =============================================================================
# 
# This file contains the recommended production settings for deploying
# HireMeBahamas frontend to Vercel with the serverless backend.
#
# IMPORTANT: This file is a template. Copy actual values to Vercel Dashboard:
# https://vercel.com/[your-team]/[project]/settings/environment-variables
#
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# API BACKEND CONFIGURATION (RENDER-ONLY)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Frontend is hard-locked to the Render backend to prevent accidental
# calls to deprecated Railway services.
#
# ✅ REQUIRED: Point to Render backend
#    VITE_API_URL=https://hiremebahamas.onrender.com
# ✅ Safety guard in code throws if this value is not an onrender.com URL
#
VITE_API_URL=https://hiremebahamas.onrender.com

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OPTIONAL FEATURES
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Cloudinary Configuration (for image uploads)
# Get credentials from: https://cloudinary.com/console
# VITE_CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME=your_cloudinary_name

# Sendbird Configuration (for advanced messaging)
# Get credentials from: https://sendbird.com/dashboard
# VITE_SENDBIRD_APP_ID=your_sendbird_app_id

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OAUTH CONFIGURATION (OPTIONAL)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 
# ⚠️  OAuth buttons are automatically hidden if these are not configured
# ⚠️  Leave commented out if you don't want OAuth sign-in
# ⚠️  Only set real values - placeholders will cause OAuth errors
#
# Google OAuth
# Get Client ID from: https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
# VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=

# Apple OAuth
# Get Client ID from: https://developer.apple.com/account/resources/identifiers
# VITE_APPLE_CLIENT_ID=

# =============================================================================
# DEPLOYMENT INSTRUCTIONS
# =============================================================================
#
# 1. VERCEL DASHBOARD SETUP:
#    - Go to: https://vercel.com/[team]/[project]/settings/environment-variables
#    - Add any VITE_* variables you need (see above)
#    - Set environment scope: Production, Preview, or Development
#
# 2. FOR VERCEL SERVERLESS BACKEND (RECOMMENDED):
#    - Do NOT set VITE_API_URL
#    - Frontend will automatically detect Vercel and use same-origin
#    - API endpoints available at: /api/*
#    - Example: https://your-project.vercel.app/api/health
#
# 3. FOR SEPARATE BACKEND (Railway, etc.):
#    - Set VITE_API_URL in Vercel Dashboard
#    - Example: VITE_API_URL=https://your-app.up.railway.app
#    - Ensure backend CORS allows your Vercel domain
#
# 4. VERIFY DEPLOYMENT:
#    - Check: https://your-project.vercel.app/api/health
#    - Should return: {"status":"healthy","platform":"vercel-serverless"}
#    - Open browser console to see detected API URL
#
# =============================================================================
